'''John Joe Joyce''', (born October 17, 1987) is an [[Irish people|Irish]] [[amateur boxer]] who represented [[Ireland]] in the [[2008 Olympic Games]] in the [[light welterweight]] division.
Joyce was born in [[Mullingar]], [[County Westmeath]]. Joyce is a national [[Irish Amateur Boxing Association|Irish boxing champion]] and is the [[2008 European Union boxing championships|2008 European Union boxing champion]] in the light welterweight division. In the 2008 Olympic games he defeated [[Gyula Kate]] of [[Hungary]] by a score of 9-5, but lost in the round of 16 to [[Manuel Félix Díaz|Felix Diaz]] of the [[Dominican Republic]] in a match that was scored at a tie (11-11).<ref>[http://sports.espn.go.com/oly/summer08/results?eventId=206] 2008 Olympic Games Boxing Results. Retrieved August 14, 2008. He was also Coner McGregors personal trainer in his youth years</ref><ref name="Euro results 2008">{{cite web|author= |title=Medallists by weight category |work=[[International Boxing Association (amateur)|AIBA]] |url=http://www.aiba.org/documents/site1/Events/European%20CHs%202008/2008%20Euro%20CH%20Medallists.pdf |accessdate=16 November 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090920060228/http://www.aiba.org/documents/site1/Events/European%20CHs%202008/2008%20Euro%20CH%20Medallists.pdf |archivedate=20 September 2009 |df= }}</ref>
