'''Lily Gladstone''' (born 1986)<ref>https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:QJYN-ST4M : 16 May 2014</ref> is an American actress.

Gladstone was born and raised in [[Browning, Montana]].<ref>http://www.makeitmissoula.com/2014/08/lily-gladstones-beautiful-future/</ref> She is of [[Piegan Blackfeet|Blackfeet]] and [[Nez Perce people|Nez Perce]] heritage.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bauer|first1=Jennifer K.|title=Staying true to her heritage: ‘Winter in the Blood’ star Lily Gladstone talks about filmmaking, bucking Hollywood stereotypes|url=http://inland360.com/more-news/2013/03/staying-true-to-her-heritage-winter-in-the-blood-star-lily-gladstone-talks-about-filmmaking-bucking-hollywood-stereotypes/|accessdate=5 October 2016}}</ref> Her "great, great grandfather was first cousin to [[William Ewart Gladstone|William Gladstone]], the British prime minister - her great, great grandfather was Kainai Chief Red Crow.<ref>Kate Kellaway,"Lily Gladstone: ‘I lived in the reservations until I was 11’" https://www.theguardian.com/film/2017/feb/12/lily-gladstone-interview-certain-women-kristen-stewart-kelly-reichardt</ref> She graduated from the [[University of Montana]] with a B.F.A in Acting. As a child she performed with the Stone Soup Theatre Company in Seattle. She has also been a member of ''Living Voices'', a touring theatre troupe.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Walsh|first1=Cory|title=Missoula actress talks 'Certain Women,' set to premiere at Sundance|url=http://missoulian.com/news/local/missoula-actress-talks-certain-women-set-to-premiere-at-sundance/article_b8780a7a-31a4-5125-bff8-723fbe07a09b.html|accessdate=5 October 2016}}</ref> Gladstone starting acting as an extra when she was a teenager. She landed her first speaking part in ''[[Jimmy P: Psychotherapy of a Plains Indian]]'', alongside [[Misty Upham]].

In 2016, her breakout role came from [[Kelly Reichardt]]'s ''[[Certain Women (film)|Certain Women]]'' playing Jamie, a lonely ranch hand, for which she won the [[Los Angeles Film Critics Association Award for Best Supporting Actress]] and [[Boston Society of Film Critics Award for Best Supporting Actress]]. She also received nominations for the [[Independent Spirit Award for Best Supporting Female]] and [[Gotham Awards|Gotham Award]] for Breakthrough Actress.

