{{Orphan|date=September 2018}}

'''Roosevelt Sanon''' is a [[Haiti|Haitian]] artist who was born in 1951 to [[Jacmel]] to Bejamine Jean-Pierre Sanon and Clément Sanon. He began painting at age 17 with no instruction. He later received mentoring from Raphaël Surin and others. His siblings Lamar and Jeannet Sanon are also painters. When he was 23, Sanon was the grand prizewinner in an art competition sponsored by the German [[embassy]] in Haiti and the ''Musée d’Art Haïtien.'' Afterwards, He traveled to [[Germany]] to study the work of European artists.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://haiti.org/an-artists-serendipitous-visit-to-the-embassy-of-haiti/|title=An Artist’s Serendipitous Visit to the Embassy of Haiti – Embassy of Haiti|website=haiti.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-05-14}}</ref> From 1979 to 1985, Sanon has exhibited his work in [[France]], [[Switzerland]], [[England]] and Haiti between 1979 and 1985.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://paddle8.com/work/roosevelt-sanon/135906-tree-in-water|title=Tree in Water by Roosevelt Sanon {{!}} Paddle8|website=paddle8.com|access-date=2018-05-14}}</ref> Some of his work is displayed in the Haitian embassy in [[Washington, D.C.|Washington, DC]].<ref name=":0" />

His better known pieces include: ''A river runs through it'', ''Mapou tree'' and ''The walking tree''.<ref name=":0" />

